    Configuring Your Microsoft Account

    by Joseph Hortezuela - Friday, 6 November 2020, 8:28 AM

    We have posted the link to the one-question survey for our Second Quarter of implementation of the remote learning delivery through MS forms but you need to sign up first using your Pisay email and configure the password at this Microsoft 365 for education account of Pisay CVisC at this link:

    https://www.microsoft.com/en-ph/education/products/office


    You need to configure your MS account for we need this in our LMS integration for video conferencing. Microsoft teams platform is similar to Discord and can notify you better of the deadlines and activities of all subjects.

    Academic Break on November 2 - 6, 2020

    by Joseph Hortezuela - Monday, 19 October 2020, 11:27 AM

    As discussed in our CID meeting last October 5 and with the approval of Dr. Rica last week, we are giving an academic break to all PSHS-CVisC students. You will no longer be required to attend synchronous / asynchronous sessions and you are free from all assignments, quizzes and projects on November 2 - 6, 2020. 

    Coincidentally, it is an answer to the Twitter Philippines trending topic #PisayGiveUsABreak. 

    Stay safe and enjoy your break, scholars!

    Community Nutrition Invitation from Philippine Association of Nutrition-Alpha Chapter (UPDiliman)

    by Jonalyn Salazar - Friday, 16 October 2020, 10:24 AM
    Hello, PSHS- CVisC students!

    "On October 17, PAN-Alpha will be holding the first Community Nutrition (CN) Promotion event, entitled RND, Set, Go!, which aims to introduce CN as a degree program, and Nutrition and Dietetics as a future profession to the general public, particularly high school students. This project aims to inform high school students about the curriculum, subjects, possible career paths, and other relevant information on Nutrition and Dietetics with the goal of encouraging them to take this program in college. This is in line with the organization’s mission of attaining a critical mass of nutritionists and dietitians who will serve the Filipino people. This event will be held on October 17, 2020 from 2:00 PM to 5:00 PM, via Zoom. 

    Registration to the event is completely free of charge and certificates will be given to the students.

    Participants may register through this link: https://forms.gle/PDtFcCSfWUoY358N7
